Timothy Miller wrote:
> Two alternatives:
>
> (a)     !!(x & 0x400)
> 
> (b)     (x & 0x400) >> 10
I like either of these:
   #define FOO_BITS 0x400
   #define test_mask(t,m) ( !!((t) & (m)) )
   ...
   return test_mask(x, FOO_BITS);
or
   return (x & FOO_BITS) != 0;
Those double exclamation points should be hidden in macros. :)
